Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Phoenix House is a four storey office building adjacent to Central Milton Keynes train station and associated amenities. The building also benefits from an exception town centre parking ratio of 1:463 sq ft, all of which are in a secure car park behind and next to a public multi-storey car park. The office accommodation available to let is on the 3rd Floor, part 1st Floor and a self-contained office suite on the Ground Floor.

Phoenix House is in a prime office location in Station Square, adjacent to Milton Keynes Central railway station. The direct journey time to London Euston is 35 minutes and Phoenix House is approximately 10 minutes’ drive from Junction 14 of the M1.

The Pinnacle totals 190,000 sq ft and comprises two adjoining “L” shape buildings (Building A and Building B) each providing two wings of  accommodation arranged around a central courtyard. The property is arranged over basement, lower ground, ground and seven upper floors. Milton Keynes benefits from excellent road connections being adjacent to the M1 (Junction 14) which links to the M25 (Junction 21/21A) to the south and in turn the national motorway network. The A5 dual carriageway runs north-west to south-east through Milton Keynes enabling direct access to key towns in the surrounding area.

Exchange House is a high quality office building, with a retail and restaurant element on the ground floor. The offices are arranged on the first to fifth floors around a central atrium and are accessed by three core areas. The property has undergone a substantial refurbishment on a number of the floors to provide high quality Grade A office accommodation. Exchange House occupies a prime position at the heart of central Milton Keynes business district in a prominent position on the corner of Midsummer Boulevard and Saxon Gate. The property is ideally situated adjacent to the extensive shopping facilities of Centre: MK and within walking distance of the railway station with leisure facilities, restaurants and hotels all close by.

New City Place occupies a prominent position at the heart of one of the UK’s fastest growing business destinations – Milton Keynes. New City Place will be situated in a prime central location along Midsummer Boulevard and under a 5 minute walk from Milton Keynes station, giving you direct access to London in 30 minutes. On completion this office led scheme will be grade A quality in the heart of Milton Keynes.
